This change to ftp_process_connection() in modules/ftp/ftp_connection.c:169 
was made in r603800 2007/12/13 01:42:34

     if (!fsc->enabled) {
-        return DECLINED;
+        return OK;

This prevents other connection handlers, like ap_process_http_connection,  from
being called.  process_connection is a HOOK_RUN_FIRST/DECLINED type hook, so
ftp_process_connection should return DECLINED to let other handlers process the
connection if possible.
